article.headline: Sacramento St. 100, UC Davis 77
article.story: SACRAMENTO, Calif. (AP) -- Haron Hargrave had 22 points, six rebounds, four assists, and three steals to lead Sacramento State to a 100-77 victory over UC Davis on Saturday night. Loren Leath led all scorers with 28 points and Alex Bausley added 13 points and six rebounds for the Hornets (4-3). Ari Warmerdam scored 16 points off the bench and Vince Oliver had 14 points and six assists for the Aggies (0-6) who have played all of their six games on the road. UC Davis gave up the ball 30 times. Leath's 3-point shot with less than 10 minutes left in the second half gave the Hornets their largest lead in the game, 72-47. Sac State led by as many as 19 points in the first after Hargrave converted a three-point play with six minutes to play. The Hornets forced 19 turnovers and had seven steals to take a 45-29 halftime lead.
